your mother to eat lots of vegetables?

272
00:17:52,667 --> 00:17:54,833
Yes. Could I?

273
00:17:54,833 --> 00:17:58,583
Very well. I will grant your wish.

274
00:17:58,583 --> 00:18:00,208
Thank you so much!

275
00:18:00,208 --> 00:18:03,292
--That's great news, Ruka-<i>kun</i>!
--Yes!

276
00:18:03,292 --> 00:18:06,333
Wouldn't changing
someone's gender be a bad idea?

277
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:10,458
Do you seriously think some vegetables
can change something like that?

278
00:18:10,458 --> 00:18:14,042
That's true. There's not
even any scientific basis for it.

279
00:18:14,042 --> 00:18:18,583
He's clearly been struggling with this.
If it'll make him feel better...

280
00:18:18,583 --> 00:18:24,083
Rukako. As of today, you
are one of us: Lab Member 006!

281
00:18:24,083 --> 00:18:25,458
R-Right!

282
00:18:25,458 --> 00:18:28,083
Now, then! Let us get
the experiment underway--

283
00:18:28,083 --> 00:18:30,417
You're 17 this year, right?

284
00:18:30,417 --> 00:18:32,042
Huh? Yes.

285
00:18:32,042 --> 00:18:35,958
Which would mean you were born in 1993...?

286
00:18:35,958 --> 00:18:37,792
Why do you ask?

287
00:18:37,792 --> 00:18:42,417
When did cell phones
start to take off in Japan?

288
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:48,250
Around 1996, it looks like.

289
00:18:48,250 --> 00:18:50,917
Ones with e-mail capabilities
might've been even later.

290
00:18:50,917 --> 00:18:53,917
In other words,
Urushibara-<i>san</i>'s mother

291
00:18:53,917 --> 00:18:57,375
might not have had a
cell phone when he was born.

292
00:18:57,375 --> 00:18:59,833
Then we can't send a D-mail?

293
00:18:59,833 --> 00:19:01,292
Oh, no...

294
00:19:01,292 --> 00:19:04,292
Maybe we could hack the microwave
to send psycho-waves instead?

295
00:19:04,292 --> 00:19:06,917
You two are all the psychos we need.

296
00:19:06,917 --> 00:19:12,292
Yes...! That's it...! Abuse me more!

297
00:19:12,292 --> 00:19:14,083
I got it...

298
00:19:16,167 --> 00:19:18,125
My genius frightens me!

299
00:19:18,125 --> 00:19:20,167
I'm afraid to ask...

300
00:19:20,167 --> 00:19:23,958
If cell phones are out, then
let's just send it to a pager!

301
00:19:23,958 --> 00:19:28,875
Pagers were miniature receivers
that signals could be sent to via phone.

302
00:19:28,875 --> 00:19:32,333
They enjoyed widespread use in the 1990s,

303
00:19:32,333 --> 00:19:35,333
but their popularity waned
after cell phones were introduced.

304
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:38,292
--Pagers?
--I've never seen one before!

305
00:19:38,292 --> 00:19:41,375
You sure know a lot. You're more
like "Celeb 30" than "Celeb 17."

306
00:19:41,375 --> 00:19:44,375
It's written right there. Read for yourself.

307
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:49,500
Lab Member 006, Urushibara Ruka!

308
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:51,167
This is your first mission.

309
00:19:51,167 --> 00:19:55,042
Find out if your mother had
a pager and obtain its number!

310
00:19:55,042 --> 00:19:56,750
R-Right!

311
00:19:58,542 --> 00:20:01,833
My mother had a pager!

312
00:20:01,833 --> 00:20:04,750
--This is the number!
--Excellent!

313
00:20:04,750 --> 00:20:07,125
You decided on the message too, I hope?

314
00:20:07,125 --> 00:20:07,875
Yes!

315
00:20:07,875 --> 00:20:11,500
"Eat vegetables for a healthy baby."

316
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:16,083
I heard you can only send
18 <i>hiragana </i>characters, so...

317
00:20:16,083 --> 00:20:18,917
You can only send
numbers to pagers, though.

318
00:20:18,917 --> 00:20:20,917
We'll have to convert this into numbers...

319
00:20:20,917 --> 00:20:22,250
Just a sec.

320
00:20:22,250 --> 00:20:25,292
It looks like voiced consonant
marks need two numbers.

321
00:20:25,292 --> 00:20:26,167
Huh?

322
00:20:26,167 --> 00:20:29,542
We can send 36 half-width
Japanese characters at most.

323
00:20:29,542 --> 00:20:31,750
That makes this message
four characters too long.

324
00:20:31,750 --> 00:20:33,667
Hmm. In that case...

325
00:20:34,667 --> 00:20:37,833
Converting this into numerical form, we get...

326
00:20:40,458 --> 00:20:43,167
--Okay! We're gonna start it up!
--Right!

327
00:20:43,167 --> 00:20:45,375
